***************************************************************************
@NODE h "history"
@{LINDENT 1}



@{B}history@{UB}


@{U}2.5@{UU}

 - pipeline filling problem on MC68060 fixed (again those halved values...)
 - frequency of CPU returned with  a single, nearest-rounded decimal  digit
 - guide updated


@{U}2.4@{UU}

 - fix for MC68060 (again)
 - "RETURNCODE" argument changed to "RETCOD"
 - guide reworked


@{U}2.3@{UU} [internal version]

 - some adjustment to my own routines library (again)
 - minor changes to output texts


@{U}2.2@{UU} [internal version]

 - simple adjustment to my own routines library


@{U}2.1@{UU} [internal version]

 - changed a bit the output (I changed my CPU/FPU detection code, and so  I
   had to re-adapt this program again...)


@{U}2.0@{UU}

 - CPU frequency calculation code improved
 - bad detection of MC68060 frequency (was doubled) corrected
 - video  refresh  rate  detection  code  improved  &  fixed  (the   EClock
   frequency value used for PAL systems was wrong)
 - commandline options added
 - returncode added
 - initialization/cleanup code totally revised
 - previous versions  did  not  exit  cleanly  if  an  MC68000/MC68010  was
   detected
 - code generally revised & polished


@{U}1.12@{UU} [internal version]

 - code re-adapted for  my own revised  routines library (nothing  special)
 - guide slightly revised


@{U}1.11@{UU} [internal version]


 - silly mistake fixed: data was forced to reside in a FAST RAM section  by
   a "data_f" instead of "data"


@{U}1.10@{UU} [internal version]

 - fixed  bad   screen  refresh   rate   detection  in   interlaced   modes
 - definitively unuseable on MC68000/MC68010
 - the program got renamed "CPUSpd" ("CPUspeed")


@{U}1.8e-1.8i@{UU} [internal versions]

 - minor revisions


@{U}1.8d@{UU} [internal version]

 - modified  to  be   compliant  to   my  own   revised  routines   library
   (now it no longer runs on MC68000/MC68010, since those new includes  use
   MC68020 instructions; moreover, they  require KS 2.04,  so it no  longer
   works under KS 1.3)


@{U}1.8b-1.8c@{UU} [internal versions]

 I made  some  mess  with revision  numbers,  so  maybe these  refer  to  a
 misterious version 1.9 I found named in an old doc...


@{U}1.8@{UU}

 - screen refresh rate detection added
 - number of rasterlines detection added
 - results now are relative to values detected


@{U}1.6@{UU}

 - major  bug  fix:  caches  handling  fixed  (crashed  on  MC68030+  CPUs)
 - MC68060's figures are no longer halved


@{U}1.2@{UU}

 - bug fix: version 1.0  crashed on MC68000/MC68010 due  to some silly  odd
   memory accesses (thanks  to Timo  Ronkko for his  detailed bug  reports)


@{U}1.1@{UU} [internal version]

 - minor changes


@{U}1.0@{UU}

 -  first public (and buggy) release
@ENDNODE
